- When I pushed on the narrowest wedge, you didn't pick one thing — you immediately redesigned the architecture: "two funnels feeding the residency, open to outside applicants." You think in systems, not features.
- "One evening, one day, one week" came out naturally when I pushed on differentiation. You didn't plan that line — it emerged from pressure. That's taste.
